circumstances.circumstancesOfRecovery:
Decedent was under home health care at his residence located at 7211 Kensington Avenue, St. Louis, Missouri 63143. His home health nurse located him unresponsive on the floor of his residence on 8/3/2022. She had least seen him the afternoon prior and ALF had complained of feeling poorly. He had a history of congestive heart failure and obesity. There was no obvious trauma or injury to ALF and the death was due to apparent natural causes. 

ALF was conveyed to the St. Louis County Medical Examiner's Office for temporary storage as there was no known family.

circumstances.circumstancesOfRecovery: Decedent discovered deceased in his residence by police after they responded for a welfare check at the request of neighbors. Decedent found on living room floor with no signs of trauma or injury. Had no known medical history and no known family. Was conveyed to the St. Louis County Medical Examiner's Office on 8/22/2022 for storage purposes. No examination was completed as this was an apparent natural death. Investigators exhausted all efforts to locate living next-of-kin and the decedent was released for county cremation on 10/25/2022 to Valhalla Funeral Chapel.

Decedent was discovered at her residence (at the above address) after neighbors contacted police for a welfare check after not being able to reach her for a scheduled outing. The decedent was  found deceased, supine in her bed, with no obvious signs of trauma or injury. She had no known medical history and no known living family. The decedent was conveyed to the St. Louis County Medical Examiner's Office on 8/9/2022 and after investigators exhausted all efforts to confirm no living family, she was released to Valhalla Funeral Chapel on  10/25/2022 for county cremation.
